<subSubSection id="C37E65015A709804FCF3F451ED85F23A" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A709804FCF3F451EA9DF3F0" blockId="7.[772,1365,3058,3479]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis id="B910EA985A709804FCF3F451EDA5F3A2" bold="true" box="[772,928,3058,3087]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C644D095A709804FC48F451ED4FF39B" authority="Broom, 1907" authorityName="Broom" authorityYear="1907" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Chrysochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sclateri">Chrysochloris sclateri Broom, 1907</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B0C3CD75A709804FCA9F3BAEA9DF3F0" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3804714318" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">Matjiesvlei, Beaufort West, Western Cape Province, South Africa.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB368A5A709804FCF3F3C7ED85F23A" blockId="7.[772,1365,3058,3479]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">
Although C. 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D095A709804FC25F3C7EA2AF328" authorityName="Broom" authorityYear="1907" box="[978,1071,3172,3205]" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Chrysochloris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sclateri">sclateri</taxonomicName>
is considered subspecifically distinct from C. 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D095A709804FB41F32CEB2DF301" baseAuthorityName="Broom" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1206,1320,3215,3244]" class="Mammalia" family="Chrysochloridae" genus="Chlorotalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="duthieae">duthieae</taxonomicName>
by some authors, it is now considered a distinct species due to consistent differences in pelage color, chromosomal properties, malleus morphology, and habitat selection. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
